              {
                "fix": "Wait until the thermometer reads 180°C before frying. Cold oil leads to greasy batter.",
                "cause": "Oil was not hot enough when the sausages went in.",
                "symptom": "The batter is greasy"
              },
              {
                "fix": "The batter should be pale gold, not white. Fry for the full 3 to 4 minutes and adjust temperature if needed.",
                "cause": "Frying time too short, or temperature too low.",
                "symptom": "The batter is very pale"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "The battered sausage is a British chip shop staple. It is ordered alongside fish and chips as a cheaper alternative or an addition. It is closely associated with Northern England and Scotland. The home version lets you choose a good pork sausage, which makes a real difference to the result.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
